Comments in addition to Bikas':

 - RMStateStore: Can you create a API for ApplicationAttemptStateDataPBImpl in YarnServerBuildUtils and use it?
 - RMAppAttempt.java: The javadoc should read ".. tokens belonging to .."
 - RMAppAttemptImpl.appAttemptTokens should simply be Token<ApplicationTokenIdentifier>, makes the semantics clear. In the state-store records, we can have a collection/ByteBuffer but not here.

I think the following in TestRMRestart verifies references and so will pass because we are using InMemory store. It is more useful to also validate the contents of the tokens. Similarly validate after RM recovery.
{code}
+    // assert application Token is saved
+    Assert.assertEquals(attempt1Token, attemptState.getAppAttemptTokens());
{code}

Move into a common function?
{code}
      Credentials credentials = new Credentials();
      Token<ApplicationTokenIdentifier> appToken = appAttempt.getApplicationToken();
      if(appToken != null){
        credentials.addToken(appToken.getService(), appToken);
      }
      Token<ClientTokenIdentifier> clientToken = appAttempt.getClientToken();
      if(clientToken != null){
        credentials.addToken(clientToken.getService(), clientToken);
      }

      ApplicationAttemptState attemptState =
          new ApplicationAttemptState(appAttempt.getAppAttemptId(),
            appAttempt.getMasterContainer(), credentials);
{code}

